        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add Slack relay mode for incoming messages",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds a third Slack connection mode, `relay`, so an OpenClaw gateway can receive Slack events from an external `openclaw-slack-router` websocket while continuing to use Slack's Web API for outbound messages.\r\n\r\nThe relay connection authenticates with a bearer token and `gatewayId`, reconnects with the existing Slack backoff policy, serializes inbound frame handling, reports connection health, and dispatches routed message events through the normal Slack message handler. Because the router has already selected the gateway from a Slack user-group mention, relay events enter the handler as authorized mentions. OpenClaw acknowledges the relay frame after message handling completes.\r\n\r\nThe router can also provide `username`, `icon_url`, or `icon_emoji` in its websocket `hello` frame. OpenClaw stores that identity per Slack account and applies it to outbound `chat.postMessage` calls unless the caller supplied an explicit identity. The default is cleared whenever the relay disconnects or the provider stops.\r\n\r\n## Configuration\r\n\r\nRelay mode adds these Slack settings at the top level or per account:\r\n\r\n- `mode: \"relay\"`\r\n- `relay.url`\r\n- `relay.authToken`, including SecretInput resolution and secret-audit support\r\n- `relay.gatewayId`\r\n\r\nRelay accounts require a bot token for outbound Slack API calls, but do not require a Slack app token or HTTP signing secret. Socket and HTTP mode behavior remains unchanged.\r\n\r\nThe change also updates Slack account inspection, setup metadata, configuration schemas, UI hints, and generated channel metadata for the new mode.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n\r\nThis separates Slack Socket Mode ownership from OpenClaw gateway behavior. A central router can maintain the Slack connection and route user-group mentions to the appropriate gateway, while each gateway keeps the existing OpenClaw Slack processing, persona, and outbound delivery path.\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n\r\n- Formatted the changed Slack implementation files with `oxfmt`.\r\n- Linted the changed Slack implementation files with `oxlint`.\r\n- Ran `git diff --check` on the identity changes.\r\n- Validated live relay delivery from Slack through the router to OpenClaw and back to Slack.\r\n- Unit tests were not run per project instruction.\r\n\r\nA broader `tsc -p extensions/slack/tsconfig.json --noEmit` attempt was blocked by the existing unrelated missing-module error in `extensions/slack/src/outbound-payload.test-harness.ts`.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1202\" height=\"958\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 18 36 45\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/477dcbad-275d-42ca-bda5-6071da865755\" />\r\n",
        "branch": "codex/slack-relay-send-identity",
